# =============================================================================
# Agentic Brain - Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env.docker and fill in your API keys
# NEVER commit .env.docker to git - it contains secrets!
# =============================================================================

# --- LLM API Keys (at least one required) ---
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your-key-here
# TOGETHER_API_KEY=your-key-here

# --- Corporate Network SSL Settings (Development Only) ---
# Uncomment these if behind corporate proxy with SSL inspection:
# PYTHONHTTPSVERIFY=0
# SSL_VERIFY=false

# --- Redis (usually leave defaults) ---
# REDIS_HOST=redis
# REDIS_PORT=6379
# REDIS_PASSWORD=BrainRedis2026

# --- Neo4j (usually leave defaults) ---
# NEO4J_PASSWORD=Brain2026

# =============================================================================
# ⚠️  WINDOWS INSTALLATION FIXES - READ THESE! ⚠️
# =============================================================================

# FIX 1: Neo4j 5.x uses server.* not dbms.* settings
# If you see "Unrecognized setting: dbms.memory.heap.max.size" - that's the old syntax!
# docker-compose.yml now uses correct Neo4j 5.x settings

# FIX 2: Port 8082 conflicts
# If Redpanda fails with "Address already in use" for port 8082, it means
# something else is using that port. We changed to 18082 by default.
# Override with: PANDAPROXY_PORT=8082 if you need the original port

# FIX 3: Redpanda memory
# Increased from 512MB to 1GB to meet recommended minimum
# Override with larger value if you have RAM: --memory=2G

# FIX 4: SSL for corporate proxies
# Set these to bypass SSL verification (DEVELOPMENT ONLY!):
# PYTHONHTTPSVERIFY=0
# SSL_VERIFY=false

# FIX 5: Redis/Kafka localhost bug
# Code now uses REDIS_HOST and KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS env vars
# Docker sets these automatically - no action needed!
